(4681, 3, '2018-03-13 06:35:48', '2018-03-13 06:35:48', '[et_pb_section bb_built="1" fullwidth="on" specialty="off" _builder_version="3.0.77"][et_pb_fullwidth_image _builder_version="3.0.77" src="/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/brn_news.jpg" show_in_lightbox="off" url_new_window="off" use_overlay="off" border_style="solid" background_position="top_left" background_repeat="repeat" background_size="initial" /][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section bb_built="1"][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.0.77" background_layout="light" border_style="solid"]\n\n<h2 class="title-red">TAY NGUYEN METAL CO., LTD - NEWS</h2>\n<h4>Ms. Le Thi Hong Yen Representative of Tay Nguyen Metal Co., Ltd. Attended Course 10</h4>\n<h4>In the morning of October 10, 2017, the Vietnam-Japan Human Resources Development Institute (VJCC-HCMC) solemnly held the Opening Ceremony of the 10th KEIEIJUKU Advanced Business Course for 28 practitioners.</h4>\nAttending the Opening Ceremony, there were guests from the Consulate General of Japan, JICA, VCCI, Japan International Cooperation Agency (JIPA), Japan External Trade Organization (FTU), Vietnam Chamber of Commerce and Industry (VSIP), Vietnam Chamber of Commerce and Industry (VSIP) Ba Ria Vung Tau, Dong Nai Young Businessmen Association and enterprises.\n\nAttending the opening ceremony, Representative of Consulate General of Japan in Ho Chi Minh City, Consul General Kawaue Junichi expressed his speech in Vietnamese. He expressed his pleasure to witness the good development of the Vietnam-Japan relationship through the visits of senior leaders of the two sides as well as economic and cultural exchanges between two countries. He emphasized the need to train entrepreneurs to master the management approach to develop supporting industries. From then on, he highlighted the role and importance of Keieijuku course in equipping practical knowledge for enterprises in this industry.\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4325" src="https://taynguyenmetal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Picture1-1.png" alt="" width="1032" height="685">\n\nDirector of the Office of the Japan International Cooperation Agency JICA in Ho Chi Minh City, Mr. Izaki Hiroshi highly appreciated the course and sent good wishes to the New Keiji students. This course has become one of the important activities of VJCC and also an important technical cooperation project of JICA in Vietnam. I highly expect that after the course you will apply what you have learned to your companies and organizations, develop leadership in the manufacturing industry in Vietnam, so that the industrialization process Vietnam will develop non-stop. In addition to conducting business courses at VJCC, in order to promote the development of supporting industries and small and medium enterprises in Vietnam, JICA also conducts credit activities to the top Equipment for improving the business environment, field counseling such as 5S guidance, technical training through vocational training institutions, and many other partnerships, contributes a a solid way for Vietnam. "\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4326" src="https://taynguyenmetal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Picture2-1.png" alt="" width="1032" height="685">\n<p style="text-align: center;">Photos: Director of JICA Office in Ho Chi Minh City - Izaki Hiroshi - speaking at the opening ceremony</p>\nKeieijuku Alumni Key 8, Le Thi Hong Yen, is the Director of Tay Nguyen Metal Limited Company. She shared from the learning process to the achievement of applying the interesting and useful knowledge from the course into the reality of the company is the revenue and profit of the company increased sharply compared to the year. before. "The best thing about learning Keieijuku is that of Toda:" There is nothing to be ashamed of when you are inferior to others, but it will be a shame when your friend today is no better than yourself. yesterday". With mindfulness "to do business from the mind", she is "imbued with the spirit of Keieijuku in executing, building her business step by step to ensure the future."\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4327" src="https://taynguyenmetal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Picture3-2.png" alt="" width="1032" height="685">\n<p style="text-align: center;">Photos: Ms. Le Thi Hong Yen speaking at the Opening Ceremony</p>\nThe opening ceremony was a joint photo session of all the guests and the new Keieijuku 10 students.\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4328" src="https://taynguyenmetal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Picture4-1.png" alt="" width="1032" height="685">\n<p style="text-align: center;">Photo: Souvenir photo taken between guest and Keieijuku practitioners course 10.</p>\n\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section bb_built="1" fullwidth="off" specialty="off" _builder_version="3.0.77" custom_padding="0px|0px|0px|0px"][et_pb_row _builder_version="3.0.77" module_class="regist"][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.0.77" background_layout="light" border_style="solid"]\n\n<h3>NEWS REGISTER</h3>\n\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="2_3"][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.0.77" background_layout="light" border_style="solid"]\n\n[mc4wp_form id="1526"]\n\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'tay nguyen metal', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tay-nguyen-metal', '', '', '2018-03-13 06:35:48', '2018-03-13 06:35:48', '', 0, 'https://taynguyenmetal.com/et_pb_layout/tay-nguyen-metal/', 0, 'et_pb_layout', '', 0),
